			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">I propose to conduct a detailed investigation into the new regimes of degenerate quantum gases whict be realised by inducing novel long-range interatomic potentials. A wide variety of these potentials can generated using particular spatial configurations of laser fields. Being able to control the interatomic potential leads to microscopic control of the properties of these gases in general, and to the tuning of pairing correlations in particular. Atoms with enhanced correlations have important applications in que logic devices and interferometry. One can also conduct basic studies into quantum liquid-like behavio using an otherwise gaseous system for which perturbative calculations can be contemplated. Calculati methods are proposed to study pairing in both Bose and Fermi systems, with investigation of the BCS. crossover being one of the main goals.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
